the use of straw as a building material largely in the American Southwest, but also in Canada, Australia, France, Holland, Germany, Austria and China. Straw is a renewable resource with excellent insulating properties. It is a cheap and easy-to-use option for self-builders, and even large-scale structures can be erected using timber framework filled with straw. This book is a practical, hands-on guide to building with straw. Fire safety, protection against moisture, damp, pests and parasites are treated in detail. Numerous on-site photos document the process of assembly and construction step by step. 30 exemplary international projects illustrate the wide spectrum of design possibilities with straw.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aBaustoff. 4aBrandsicherheit. 4aNachhaltige Baumaterialien. 4aNässeschutz. 4aStroh. 4aStrohballen. 4aStrohballenbauweise. 4aStrohbauten. 4anachhaltig Bauen. 4anachwachsender Baustoff. 4anachwachsendes Baumaterial. 4anatürlicher Baustoff. 4apraxisnah. 4aumweltbewusste Architektur. 4aökologisch. 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh  aSustainable architecture.  astraw buildings.  astraw insulation.1 aKrick, Benjamin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyter